<ext_description linkend="Layered_2d_shape_mim.planar_curve_constraint">
The <b>planar_curve_constraint</b> rule constrains the dimensionality of a
<express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.shape_representation"/> when it is only allowed to include planar curves.
</ext_description>

<ext_description linkend="Layered_2d_shape_mim.planar_curve_constraint.wr:WR1">
If the name of a <express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.shape_representation"/> is 'planar projected shape',
'bevel edge feature shape','step edge feature shape' or 
'radius edge feature shape' then dimensionality of the geometric
context shall be exactly 2.
</ext_description>

